label new_customer_1:
    "Just then, there's a tap at the front door. There's a middle aged man standing there."
    "You look at Ingram, who confirms that he's a customer and to let him in."
    "You walk over and unlock the door, offering him to make a drink."
    "He chooses a latte, and Ingram tasks you with making it."
    "You nervously prepare the drink, trying to remember everything Ingram taught you."
    "Once it's ready, you hand it to the man and he takes a sip, enjoying it with a hearty chuckle."
    "Ingram explains the process of spirit guiding to him, which spurs the man to share his own story."
    "The two of you learn that his name is Brio and that he passed away from cancer."
    "He tells you about his life as a musician and luthier."
    "He grew up spending a lot of time in his grandfather's shop, who was also a luthier."
    "His grandfather was the biggest reason why he grew to love music so much."
    "When his parents pushed for a different career direction, it was his grandfather who had wholeheartedly supported his musical career."
    "When it came time for Brio's first big performance, he sent a letter to his grandfather inviting him to the concert."
    "However, his grandfather never showed up. He was devastated."
    "He later found out that his grandfather had actually tried to make it."
    "But because Brio was all caught up in the moment, he never thought to check in with him and his grandfather had ended up getting lost on the way to the venue."
    "Because of this one regret, Brio wishes he could go back in time and find his grandfather."
    "After that performance, his grandfather's health rapidly declined, and he passed away not long after."
    "After hearing Brio's story, you feel a pang of sympathy for him."
    "After Brio finishes his latte, he thanks you and Ingram for listening to him."
    "The three of you head to the Sweven Mirror to help spirit guide Brio."
    scene blank with bgwipe
    scene sweven_mirror with bgwpe
    show ingram with dissolve
    "You arrive at the Sweven Mirror with Brio and Ingram."
    "Ingram begins the spirit guiding process, and you watch as Brio steps into the mirror."
    "A warm light envelops him, and you see a look of peace wash over him."
    "After he disappears, Ingram turns to you."
    "Ingram explains that since this is the first time you'll be actively involved in spirit guiding, he'll help walk you through the process."
    "He explains the importance of being present and mindful during spirit guiding."
    "That they are there to help the customer find closure and peace. But things don't always go as planned, and not to beat yourself up if you don't achieve that goal."
    "If you're ever confused on what to do, just step aside and try mentally calling on him for guidance."
    "He'll still be there, watching over you."
    "You nod, taking in Ingram's words."
    "With that, Ingram prompts you to step into the mirror to begin spirit guiding."
    scene swevenlight with swevenwipe_cw
    pause(0.5)
    scene blank with fade
    return